# BROWSER-notifications.md - Mentions, Reply Verification & Follow

## § 2 — Extract Mentions

Returns only `url` (for grep dedup) and `handle` (for reply context). Filters out our own tweets.
🚨 Includes embedded 2s wait — do NOT add separate `exec sleep` before this.

```javascript
// Use on https://x.com/notifications/mentions — embedded 2s wait
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => {
      const mentions = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
      resolve({
        count: mentions.length,
        items: mentions.slice(0, 15).map(article => {
          const user = article.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]');
          const link = article.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
          return {
            url: link ? 'https://x.com' + link.getAttribute('href') : '',
            handle: user ? (user.innerText.split('\\n').find(l => l.startsWith('@')) || '') : ''
          };
        }).filter(m => m.url && m.handle !== '@{{handle_slug}}')
      });
    }, 2000));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

## § 2b — Combined Thread Context + Like (on tweet page)

After navigating to a mention tweet, extract thread context AND like in ONE evaluate. Includes embedded 2s wait (do NOT use separate `exec sleep`):

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => {
      const articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
      // Find target tweet by status ID (partial match — Twitter may redirect/append /photo/1)
      const statusId = '${tweetUrl}'.match(/status\\/([\\d]+)/)?.[1] || '';
      const target = articles.find(a => {
        const link = a.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
        return link && link.getAttribute('href')?.includes(statusId);
      });
      if (!target) { resolve({ error: 'tweet not found', count: articles.length }); return; }

      // Extract text
      const text = target.querySelector('[data-testid="tweetText"]')?.innerText || '';

      // Like (if not already liked)
      let liked = false;
      const likeBtn = target.querySelector('[data-testid="like"]');
      if (likeBtn) { likeBtn.click(); liked = true; }
      else if (target.querySelector('[data-testid="unlike"]')) { liked = true; }

      // Check if we already replied (look for @{{handle_slug}} in replies below)
      const targetIdx = articles.indexOf(target);
      const alreadyReplied = articles.slice(targetIdx + 1).some(a => {
        const handle = a.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]')?.innerText?.split('\\n').find(l => l.startsWith('@'));
        return handle === '@{{handle_slug}}';
      });

      // Count our total replies in this thread (depth check)
      var ourReplyCount = articles.filter(a => {
        var h = a.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]')?.innerText?.split('\\n').find(l => l.startsWith('@'));
        return h === '@{{handle_slug}}';
      }).length;
      var tooDeep = ourReplyCount >= 3;

      resolve({ text, liked, alreadyReplied, ourReplyCount, tooDeep });
    }, 2000));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `alreadyReplied` → track and skip. Otherwise proceed with CDP typing (§ 1).

## § 6 — Reply Verification (MANDATORY — never skip)

🚨 ALWAYS verify after EVERY reply. Skipping leads to phantom replies tracked but never posted.

```javascript
// After posting reply — embedded 1.5s wait, then verify
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => {
      const articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
      const statusId = '${tweetUrl}'.match(/status\/([\d]+)/)?.[1] || '';
      let targetIdx = -1;
      articles.forEach((article, idx) => {
        const link = article.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
        if (link && link.getAttribute('href')?.includes(statusId)) targetIdx = idx;
      });
      const hasOurReply = articles.slice(targetIdx + 1).some(article => {
        const handle = article.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]')?.innerText.split('\\n').find(l => l.startsWith('@'));
        return handle === '@{{handle_slug}}';
      });
      resolve({ success: hasOurReply });
    }, 1500));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

## § 11 — Follow User (from tweet page — no navigation needed)

🚨 **MANDATORY after every promo and strategic reply.** Every engagement = follow. Button on tweet page: `[data-testid$="-follow"]` → after click: `[data-testid$="-unfollow"]`.

```javascript
// Use on tweet page — already there after replying. ONE evaluate, no navigation.
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    // Find ALL follow buttons, pick the topmost one (tweet author, not commenters)
    const btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-testid$="-follow"]'));
    if (!btns.length) return { alreadyFollowing: true };
    const topBtn = btns.reduce((best, b) =>
      b.getBoundingClientRect().y < best.getBoundingClientRect().y ? b : best
    );
    topBtn.click();
    return { followed: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `alreadyFollowing`: skip silently. If error: skip follow, don't block engagement.
